Vice President Biden and Secretary of Education Arne Duncan hosted two conference calls with governors, mayors, and a county official to discuss the implementation of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act. Participating officials included Governor Charlie Crist (R-FL), Governor Dave Freudenthal (D-WY), Governor Bob Riley (R-AL), Governor Bill Ritter (D-CO), Mayor Greg Ballard (R-Indianapolis, IN), Mayor Cory Booker (D- Newark, NJ), Mayor David Cicilline (D-Providence, RI), Mayor John DeStefano (D-New Haven, CT), and County Commissioner Lenny Eliason (D-Athens County, OH).